    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "ABOUT THE COMPANY\n\nAt Thrill Labs, we're not just building a gaming company; we're creating a global sensation. We are the innovative force behind Thrill.com http://Thrill.com, a groundbreaking crypto gaming venture set to launch soon! Our mission? To build the world’s most epic gaming brand and craft magical experiences for millions of users. Backed by a world-class team, we’re here to redefine the future of gaming.﻿\n\nAbout the role\nWe are seeking for a Senior/Lead Back End Software Engineers with building Sportsbook from scratch to join our brand new Sportsbook team we are building. In this role, you will be a crucial player in our growth, responsible for the end-to-end software development cycle, from framing product requirements and designing to testing and maintaining deployments for Sportsbook.\n\nYour contributions will be critical in shaping our product and architecture, ensuring high-quality deliverables in an agile environment. This is a unique opportunity to work on cutting-edge solutions and build robust backend systems that power our platform.\n\nWhat You’ll Be Doing:\n\n - Design, develop, and maintain scalable and efficient software solutions for our new Sportsbook platform\n\n - Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather requirements and translate them into technical specifications.\n\n - Troubleshoot and debug technical issues.\n\n - Lead architectural discussions and make informed technology decisions to improve system performance and reliability.\n\n - Conduct reviews, ensuring adherence to best practices and coding standards.\n\nWhat You’ll Need:\n\n - Proven experience in building Sports betting application from scratch\n\n - 7+ years of software development experience, with a strong background in Java/Kotlin and Spring.\n\n - Experience leading the design and implementation of large-scale software systems, particularly with a focus on distributed systems.\n\n - Experience with AWS.\n\n - Experience building CI/CD pipelines.\n\n - Good communication skills, capable of explaining technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.\n\n - Good command of English (at least B2 equivalent).\n\nWhy Join Us?\nAt Thrill Labs, your creativity will shape the future of entertainment products. This is more than a job; it’s an opportunity to leave your mark on a global stage. If you’re ready to take on the challenge, push boundaries, and build a brand like no other, we want you on our team.\n\nReady to Create the Next Big Thing? Apply Now!",
